HEADWORD: Descendibility
<hw>De*scend`i*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
quality of being descendible; capability of being transmitted from
ancestors; <as>as, the <ex>descendibility</ex> of an
estate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Descendible</ent>⟦br⟧
